==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ascarid
<hw>As"ca*rid</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Ascarides</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr> or <er>Ascarids</er>.</plu>
<ety>[NL. <ets>ascaris</ets>, fr. Gr. <?/.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A parasitic nematoid worm, especially the roundworm, <spn>Ascaris
lumbricoides</spn>, often occurring in the human intestine, and allied
species found in domestic animals; also commonly applied to the pinworm
(<gen>Oxyuris</gen>), often troublesome to children and aged
persons.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ascaridae</ent>⟦br⟧
